<% provide(:title, 'Interest Rates') %>

<div id="slide">
  <h2>What can Interest Rates realistically EARN you?</h2>
    <p>
      Let&apos;s look at some actual interest rates that you can actually expect to earn. Remember, these rates are just approximations. The actual rate you will earn, can vary depending on the length of the investment and the amount of your payments.
    </p> 

    <p>
      Further, in the example of stocks, this rate is variable and at no point a guarantee. The higher the risk the greater the variance of the returns.
    </p>

    <p>
      Test out the following input Interest Rates:
    </p>

    <table class="approx_irates">
      <tr>
        <th>Checking Account</th>
        <th>Certified Deposit</th>
        <th>Treasury Bonds</th>
        <th>Stocks</th>
        <th>Question 1</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>.04%</td>
        <td>.08%</td>
        <td>1.8%</td>
        <td>13%</td>
        <td>25%</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

  <div class="earn" id="irate_form">
    <form  method=post id="iRateForm">
    <table>
      <tr>
        <td>Monthly Investments:</td>
        <td><input class="required" id="pmt" type=number size=13 maxlength=13></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Length of Monthly Investments:</td>
        <td><input class="required" id="numOfPeriods" type=number size=6 maxlength=3>
          <select id="yearOrMonth" size=1>
            <option value="y">Years
            <option value="m">Months
          </select>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Interest Rate:</td>
        <td><input class="required" type=number id="interest" size=6 maxlength=5><b> %</b></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="center" colspan = "2">
          <button class="button" id="howMuch">
            Earnings
          </button>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Total Savings with Interest:</td>
        <td>
          <input id="totalInterest" type=text name=total value="0.00" size=20>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Total Savings with out Interest:</td>
        <td>
          <input id="totalNoInterest" type=text name=total value="0.00" size=20>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Extra Income:</td>
        <td>
          <input id="difference" type=text name=total value="0.00" size=20>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    </form>
  </div>

  <div id="chart_container">
    <%= render 'shared/default_graph' %>
    <div id="legend" class="rickshaw_legend">
      <ul><li class="line"><div class="swatch" style="background-color: rgb(173, 216, 230);"></div><span class="label">Interest Income</span></li><li class="line"><div class="swatch" style="background-color: rgb(70, 130, 180);"></div><span class="label">No Interest Income</span></li></ul>
    </div>
  </div>

    <div class="bottom_left">
      <%= link_to "Back", slide5_path, class: "button" %>
    </div>

    <div class="bottom_right">
      <%= link_to "Next", slide7_path, class: "button" %>
    </div>
</div>
